article.description: Mitch Mersman connected on his third field goal of the game, this one from 22-yards out with :01 left in the game, to lift Tennessee-Martin to a 16-14 win over Southeast Missouri State in an Ohio Valley Conference battle Saturday.
article.headline: Mersman's late FG lifts UT Martin past SE Missouri St, 16-14
article.linkText: Mersman's late FG lifts UT Martin past SE Missouri St, 16-14
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Mitch Mersman connected on his third field goal of the game, this one from 22-yards out with :01 left in the game, to lift Tennessee-Martin to a 16-14 win over Southeast Missouri State in an Ohio Valley Conference battle Saturday. The win gives UT Martin (5-4, 3-3) back-to-back wins after snapping a season-long three-game losing streak. Jesse Hosket staked the Redhawks to the lead with a 12-yard run in the first quarter, then put them in the lead, 14-13, with a five-yard pass to Logan Larson on the first play of the fourth quarter. Freshman Dresser Winn completed 12 of 23 pass attempts for 224 yards and the Skyhawks' lone touchdown, a 10-yard strike to Londell Lee. UT Martin had 420 total yards while holding the Redhawks (2-7, 2-4) to just 307, 86 yards passing. Marquis Terry had 20 carries for 154 yards to spearhead the offense for SE Missouri. --- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
